com.googlecode.cqengine.attribute.support

Class FunctionalMultiValueAttribute<O,A,I extends Iterable<A>>

  • java.lang.Object

      • com.googlecode.cqengine.attribute.MultiValueAttribute<O,A>
        • com.googlecode.cqengine.attribute.support.FunctionalMultiValueAttribute<O,A,I>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Attribute<O,A>

    public class FunctionalMultiValueAttribute<O,A,I extends Iterable<A>>
extends MultiValueAttribute<O,A>
    A MultiValueAttribute which wraps a MultiValueFunction, for the purpose of allowing attributes to be created from lambda expressions.

    These attributes can be created via QueryFactory.attribute(Class, MultiValueFunction).

    Author:
    npgall
